title: Pokémon
body:
Pikachu, an Electric-type Pokémon, is known for its ability to generate powerful electricity. It's the mascot of the Pokémon franchise.
Raichu evolves from Pikachu when exposed to a Thunder Stone. It has a greater electrical capacity.
Alolan Raichu has a dual Electric/Psychic-type and surfs on its tail, using psychic powers.
Pichu, the pre-evolution of Pikachu, can be quite playful and is often seen practicing its electric skills.
Togepi is known for its positive energy and bringing happiness. It evolves into Togetic.
Togetic evolves from Togepi when it is exposed to great happiness and evolves into Togekiss.
Plusle, a cheerleading Pokémon, works well in pairs and supports its partners in battle.
Minun, often seen with Plusle, specializes in providing support and boosting its allies' morale.
Charizard is a Fire/Flying-type Pokémon known for its powerful fire attacks and flying capabilities.

title: Starwars
body:
Luke Skywalker, a legendary Jedi, played a key role in the Galactic Civil War.
Darth Vader, formerly Anakin Skywalker, was a powerful Sith Lord.
Emperor Palpatine masterminded the rise of the Galactic Empire and was the Sith Master of Darth Vader.
Yoda, one of the most powerful Jedi Masters, trained generations of Jedi, including Luke Skywalker.
Obi-Wan Kenobi, a wise and skilled Jedi, mentored both Anakin and Luke Skywalker.
Mace Windu was a senior member of the Jedi Council, known for his skill in combat and his purple lightsaber.
Princess Leia, a leader of the Rebel Alliance, was strong in the Force and the twin sister of Luke Skywalker.
Han Solo, a daring smuggler and hero of the Rebel Alliance, piloted the Millennium Falcon.
Chewbacca, a loyal Wookiee and co-pilot of the Millennium Falcon, was a key ally to the Rebel Alliance.

title: Programing
body:
C is a powerful general-purpose programming language developed in the 1970s.
C++ is an extension of C that includes object-oriented features.
C# is a language developed by Microsoft that is similar to Java and heavily used in .NET.
Java is a widely-used object-oriented language known for its portability across platforms.
Scala is a high-level language that combines object-oriented and functional programming.
Groovy is an agile and dynamic language for the Java platform.
Objective-C is the main programming language used by Apple for macOS and iOS development before Swift.
JavaScript is a high-level, often just-in-time compiled language that conforms to the ECMAScript specification.
Python is a high-level, interpreted language known for its readability and wide range of applications.
Ruby is a dynamic, open source programming language with a focus on simplicity and productivity.
Perl is a high-level, general-purpose, interpreted, dynamic programming language.
R is a language and environment for statistical computing and graphics.
PHP is a popular general-purpose scripting language that is especially suited to web development.
